The FDA is warning consumers about health fraud scams related to COVID-19. They are cautioning against purchasing and using medical products or devices that have not been proven safe and effective. The FDA and the Federal Trade Commission have already issued warning letters to seven companies for selling fraudulent COVID-19 products, such as teas, essential oils, tinctures, and colloidal silver. The FDA is closely monitoring the sale of products making false claims related to COVID-19, including herbal products, ayurvedic medicines, protective masks, and hand sanitizers. They are working with major retailers to remove fraudulent products from online marketplaces and taking action against unscrupulous actors.